article.description: No. 18 Princeton women remain undefeated; beat Cornell 75-47
article.headline: No. 18 Princeton women remain undefeated; beat Cornell 75-47
article.linkText: No. 18 Princeton women remain undefeated; beat Cornell 75-47
article.story:
PRINCETON, N.J. --  Alex Wheatley and Michelle Miller scored 14 points apiece as No. 18 Princeton beat Cornell 75-47 on Saturday to remain one of two unbeaten teams in women's basketball.

Princeton (21-0, 5-0 Ivy) matched its longest win streak in program history, set in the 2009-10 season, and extended its Ivy League record-start.

Wheatley was 7 of 8 from the field with eight rebounds and Miller went 6 for 10 and grabbed 11 boards. Taylor Williams added 10 points and four blocks for the Tigers.

Miller scored 10 first-half points as Princeton held a 35-17 advantage after holding Cornell to 8-of-33 shooting (24.2 percent).

Nia Marshall led Cornell (13-7, 4-2) with 14 points. Nicholle Aston had 12 and Kerri Moran 11. The Big Red made 34.9 percent of their shots and were outrebounded 42-29.

Top-seeded and fellow undefeated South Carolina (22-0) faces No. 2 UConn on Monday.
